## Network Fundamentals

### Network Types
| Type | Full Name | Example |
|---|---|---|
| LAN | Local Area Network | Office or home |
| MAN | Metropolitan Area Network | City-wide cell towers |
| WAN | Wide Area Network | The global internet |
| PAN | Personal Area Network | Bluetooth earphones |

### Network Metrics
| Metric | Definition |
|---|---|
| Latency | Time for data to travel from source to destination |
| Bandwidth | Amount of data that can travel in one second |
| Throughput | Actual real-world internet speed |
| Jitter | Fluctuations and instability in network connection |

### Network Topologies
| Topology | Description | Real-world use |
|---|---|---|
| Star | All devices connect to a central router/hub | Home Wi-Fi |
| Bus | Devices connect sequentially to a single cable | School computer labs |
| Ring | Systems connect in a continuous circle | Industrial machines |
| Mesh | Every device connects to every other device | Military communications |

