## Models and Encapsulation

### OSI Model (7 Layers)
| Layer | Name | Function |
|---|---|---|
| 7 | Application | User interface |
| 6 | Presentation | Data formatting and encryption |
| 5 | Session | Checks communication channel is open |
| 4 | Transport | TCP and UDP data delivery |
| 3 | Network | IP addresses and routing |
| 2 | Data Link | MAC addresses |
| 1 | Physical | Cables, routers, hardware |

### TCP/IP Model (4 Layers)
Application → Transport → Internet → Network Access

Combines OSI layers 5, 6, 7 into one Application layer and OSI layers 1, 2 into Network Access.

### Encapsulation and Decapsulation
- **Encapsulation** — data receives a header at each layer as it travels (like adding tape and a label to a parcel)
- **Decapsulation** — headers are removed at the destination to read the data

