## Routing, NAT, and Global Connectivity

- **NAT** — converts private IP to public IP for internet communication
- **PAT** — upgraded NAT, assigns multiple port identities to a single public IP allowing multitasking
- **Routing Table** — routers evaluate Next Hop and Metric (cost/efficiency) to decide the best path

### Routing Protocols
| Protocol | Function |
|---|---|
| OSPF | Finds shortest and fastest path using Link State Advertisements |
| EIGRP | Hybrid protocol evaluating bandwidth, delay, load, and reliability |
| IS-IS | Massive enterprise backbone routing, hierarchical and scalable |
| BGP | Global internet protocol connecting Autonomous Systems across ISPs worldwide |

