## Transport Layer and Ports

### TCP vs UDP
| Protocol | Method | Use case |
|---|---|---|
| TCP | Three-Way Handshake (SYN, SYN-ACK, ACK) — guaranteed delivery | Secure communication |
| UDP | No handshake — fast, no delivery guarantee | Streaming, VoIP, gaming |

### Data Fragmentation
When a file exceeds the MTU (Maximum Transmission Unit) it is broken into smaller packets, sent across the network, and reassembled at the destination.

### Ports
- Over 56,000 ports available
- Around 1,000 commonly active (e.g. HTTP port 80, FTP port 21)
- Virtual endpoints that sort data for specific applications

