## Network Automation and Programmability

**Why automate?** Manual configuration is slow, repetitive, and error-prone.

- **REST and NETCONF APIs** — push configuration updates across thousands of devices simultaneously
- **Infrastructure as Code (IaC)** — manage networks using scripts instead of manual hardware setup
- **Terraform** — deploys network changes using scripts and Git repositories
- **Ansible** — open-source configuration tool by Michael DeHaan (2012), maintained by RedHat
- **Intent-Based Networking** — upcoming AI-driven approach that automates and predicts network operations

